ce Against Women: An Integrated, Ecological Framework. Violence against women, 4. doi:10.1177/1077801298004003002 Individual S o c i e t y C o m m u n i t y F a m i l y / R e l a t i o n s h i p 22 and programming. The commitments to CEDAW21 have compelled the elimination of all forms of discrimination against women since 1981. Recently, the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) \u2013 specifically Goal 5: Achieve gender equality and empower all women and girls and Target 5.2: Eliminate all forms of VAWG in the public and private spheres, including trafficking and sexual and other types of exploitation \u2013 provide an imperative to actively promote gender equality, including eliminating all forms of VAWG.22 Prevention of Violence Against Women and Girls Prevention of VAWG is based on a strategy of addressing the underlying causal and risk factors driving VAWG perpetration in order to prevent such violence from occurring in the first place.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c2e79585-0dee-43d3-8243-e2741c5fa254": {"__data__": {"id_": "c2e79585-0dee-43d3-8243-e2741c5fa254", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Promising strides toward ending violence against women and girls in the Asia and the Pacific Region", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "5d7197a46695103bc28baaa047bed2395e4159698a60d83c09a1df606aa1d163"}, "2": {"node_id": "12cf7833-37d0-46ed-91ac-e6b8e96b398a", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7b37b81febee7547705a40687da232733a1aecd65e78556b99546d1f0abc8666"}}, "hash": "da097b9a7bb4f8bcf3dac7c79ffd4f3e1eea1d7258bcf9fde77990c6bf928bbe", "text": "Multiple large-scale studies have shown that there is no single factor or pathway determining VAWG perpetration, but rather that it emerges from multiple interacting factors across various levels of the social ecological model.23 That is, individual factors, relationship and family factors, community factors and broader social factors all play a role. At the core of effective primary prevention of VAWG is challenging prevailing norms around gender including gender inequality and power imbalances between men and women and problematic hegemonic gender roles and identities.24 Violence Against Women and Girls Prevention Interventions Recent evidence reviews have identified effective and promising intervention approaches for VAWG prevention and include:25 1. Microfinance and gender transformative interventions 2. Relationship-level interventions (e.g. for people in intimate relationships) 3. Group programmes and community outreach 4. Community mobilization programmes to change social norms 5. Parenting programmes 6. Whole school programmes Further, lessons from programming offer important insights into key success strategies 21 http://www.un.org/womenwatch/daw/cedaw/ 22 https://sustainabledevelopment.un.org/sdg5 23 Ellsberg, M., Arango, D. J., Morton, M., Gennari, F., Kiplesund, S., Contreras, M., & Watts, C. (2015). Prevention of violence against women and girls: what does the evidence say? Lancet, 385. doi:10.1016/s0140-6736 (14) 61703-7; UN Women (2015). A Framework to Underpin Action to Prevention Violence Against Women. New York: UN Women Headquarters; Fulu,", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c00ab921-f4cf-46ce-9fd3-b47f2495cbaa": {"__data__": {"id_": "c00ab921-f4cf-46ce-9fd3-b47f2495cbaa", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Promising strides toward ending violence against women and girls in the Asia and the Pacific Region", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "9219ae1c049be1b96cca6689d3ad57b019142d99257a77a3f7efe5f8e2dd21c1"}, "3": {"node_id": "10e0bb6c-0895-420d-870a-b04a8d684658", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/promising-strides-toward-ending-violence-against-women-and-girls-asia-and-pacific-region", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "92fec80895e70d1ae7360a36b6f79b48cacffa81b8369d172d4005e5e3f65692"}}, "hash": "356ed820abafb3b66e3f3785894b6870ffd761c6fd0a2ef251c48f4fe666dbc9", "text": "E. & Heise, L. (2015). What works to prevent vio