nd adaptation targets under the Paris Agreement, adopted in 2015 during COP21 of the UNFCCC. Once the countries ratifed the Paris Agreement, the contributions become known as National Determined Contribution (NDC)5. Table 3 shows how the countries presented their mitigation and adaptation targets. In the case of the NDCs as shown in table 3, the mitigation targets vary between the countries. In the case of Colombia and Guatemala, the range represents the ambition between the unconditional and conditional targets. Nepal was the only country which did not present a general target. In the case of adaptation, how the target is presented also varies. Mostly, countries prioritized actions or", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "2d5f457c-a5ae-4cd8-92e8-d68e129d7591": {"__data__": {"id_": "2d5f457c-a5ae-4cd8-92e8-d68e129d7591", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/review-domestic-data-sources-climate-finance-flows-recipient-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Review of Domestic Data Sources for Climate Finance Flows in Recipient Countries", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/review-domestic-data-sources-climate-finance-flows-recipient-countries", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f94bbad411b4d3c8caa04908a77ee3ab8bd28ca1adc98f63106741fa113f4049"}, "3": {"node_id": "bfd69973-5d9c-41a0-9854-12d969376c7c", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/review-domestic-data-sources